<br><br>
	
<b>2011 December 03    125th FFA monthly interclub practice at UAP</b><br><br><br>


All are invited to the 125th FFA monthly interclub Aikido practice on Saturday, 2011 December 03. This series of joint monthly practice sessions started in 2000.<br><br> 

<FONT style="BACKGROUND-COLOR:#FFFFD4">
<i>SPECIAL NOTICE REGARDING SPECIAL CONDITIONS:<br><br>

This is the first time that the FFA's monthly interclub practice will be held at this venue. This particular interclub practice will be part of a special martial arts festival organized by the students of the University of Asia and the Pacific. (See the invitation letter <a href="125thInterclub-InvitationLetter.pdf" target=_blank>here</a>.) This represents a welcome opportunity to propagate aikido to a new potential recruiting pool.<br><br>

At the same time, however, we must all take note that the UAP is a socially conservative institution that has certain rules about dress, among other rules.<br><br>

The university's particular dress code affects us who will participate in the 125th interclub practice. The requirements are not particularly difficult to comply with; but it's equally easy to fall afoul of them, and to be barred from entry as a consequence, thus needlessly wasting a trip for the heedless. See the dress code declaration <a href="125thInterclub-dresscode.pdf" target=_blank>here</a>.</i><br><br><br>

</font>



DETAILS:<br><br>

MAT CONTRIBUTION:<br>   
PhP100<br><br>

DATE AND TIME:<br>
Saturday, 2011 December 03<br>
1800 hrs (6:00 p.m.)<br><br> 

(Please note the time; this is 30 minutes earlier than the usual starting time due to special circumstances.)<br><br>

THIS MONTH'S HOST:<br>
Jitsuyo Bugei Aikido Club<br><br> 

THIS MONTH'S VENUE:<br>
<a href="125thinterclub-UAPmap.pdf" target=_blank>University of Asia and the Pacific</a><br>
Ortigas Centre, Pasig City<br><br>

ALL REGARDLESS OF ORGANIZATIONAL AFFILIATION ARE WELCOME. For more details, e-mail macaikido@yahoo.com  or call 890-1976 or 77.<br><br>

Questions? Call Sebastian Santos at 890-1976 or 77.<br><br>

